to start run: trip of life.pyw

left click - add cell
right click - remove cell
mouse wheel - increase/decrease draw size
space - start/stop trip
N - next step
del - reset trip
enter - create a new trip
S - save
L - load
C - toggle cursor

Full cells are alive, empty cells are dead

The colors for full cells mean:
Red - to many neighbours, will die.
Blue - to few neighbours, will die.
Green - will survive.

And for empty cells:
Red - to many neighbours, won't spawn.
Blue - to few neighbours, won't spawn.
Green - will spawn.


Written in python 2.7 with the pyglet multimedia library.

